there is maybe more to do :
what if we want to set background for a View with 'Default-568h@2x' ? 

the path will not be found because we have to search in the  Main Bundle.

please have a look at :

 TiUtils.m
+(UIImage*)loadBackgroundImage:(id)image forProxy:(TiProxy*)proxy

and

UIModule.m
+(UIImage*)loadBackgroundImage:(id)image forProxy:(TiProxy*)proxy

in both methods we have :

if (resultImage==nil && [image isEqualToString:@"Default.png"])
        {

            // special case where we're asking for Default.png and it's in Bundle not path

            resultImage = [UIImage imageNamed:image];
        
}

btw this should also not work with Ipad Default-*.png
